Class ParamExternalsTest<R>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    R - the type of result this test operates on.

    public abstract class ParamExternalsTest<R>
extends ParamFineGrainTest<R>
    Test with external inputs. This test behaves exactly like ParamFineGrainTest. The only difference is that the test data provider is predefined and works with external inputs specified by passing -DexternalTestsPath=/path/to/files to the VM.

    Test result files are stored locally for each module under src/test/resources/external *
    Author:
    ldc

    • Method Detail

      • testData

        public static Collection<Object[]> testData()
        The data provider for this test. The input paths are calculated based off the external path provided. The results are constructed using the entire path of the input so that the result folder structure mirrors that of the external inputs.

        This method collects all sources in the provided path. If you with to do some kind of preliminary filtering, you must call it from within your own provider.
        Returns:
        a collection of test input and result paths in the form of {filename ,filepath, resultpath} arrays
